deck: Actress who has appeared in Iron Man II and who portrays Psylocke in X-Men Apocalypse.
description:
Biography

Olivia Munn is an American actress, author, model and internet personality. Born in Oklahoma City, Oklahoma, in 1980. Her parents of mixed ethnicities, including Vietnamese, American, English, German and Scottish. Munn attended University of Oklahoma and has a major in journalism and worked as a television journalist before more acting roles and pursuits.

The actress has cited her favorite comic series of all time is Y the Last Man, and her favorite comic character as Rogue.

Acting Profile

Olivia Munn has had small roles in television shows, such as Beyond the Break, and Attack of the Show later adding full length movies to her resume. Notable works include Attack of the Show, The Daily Show, The Babymakers, Iron Man 2 and most recently X-Men: Apocalypse.

Comic Related Movie Roles

Psylocke

Olivia Munn stars as the mutant Psylocke (Elizabeth Braddock) in 2016's X-Men Apocalypse. Unlike the comic she first appears as an antagonist, and one of Apocalypse's (Oscar Isaac) Horseman of the Apocalypse. She portrays Pestilence, alongside actress Alexandra Shipp as Storm/Famine, actor Michael Fassbender as Magneto/War and actor Ben Hardy as Angel/Death.

Chess Roberts

Olivia Munn has a small role as Chess Roberts in the 2010 Disney Marvel movie Iron Man II, as a character reporting and covering a Stark Expo.
